                    <row>
                        <cell rend="tdLeft">women</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdCom"/>
                        <cell rend="tdCentre">What are those women doing there? – They are baking
                            bread.</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdRight">ǝš-da-ysawwūn ysawwan haḏōlāk <hi rend="red">in-nǝswān</hi>? – gāʕǝd yxubzūn / gāʕǝd yxubzan / gāʕdāt yxubzan / gāʕdīn
                            yxubzūn.</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdID">Was machen jene Frauen dort? – Sie backen Brot.</cell>
                        <cell>ماذا تفعل أولئك النساء؟هن يخبزن.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell rend="tdLeft">husband</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdCom"/>
                        <cell rend="tdCentre">My husband wears a white shirt. We have a white
                            car.</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdRight">yǝlbas <hi rend="red">raǧli</hi> qamīṣ ʔabyað̣ w-ʔāni
                            ʔalbas badla bēð̣a.</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdID">Mein Mann trägt ein weißes Hemd und ich trage ein weißes
                            Kleid.</cell>
                        <cell>يلبس زوجي قميصا أبيض وأنا ألبس فستانا أبيض.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell rend="tdLeft">friend</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdCom"/>
                        <cell rend="tdCentre">Who is this man? – He is my friend.</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdRight">mǝnu hāḏa r-rǝǧǧāl? – huwwa <hi rend="red">ṣadīq</hi>i.</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdID">Wer ist dieser Mann? – Er ist mein Freund.</cell>
                        <cell>من هذا الرجل؟هو صديقي.</cell>
                    </row>
